During this AB, Ruth made a valiant effort to catch Judge's long foul, crashing into the RF concrete wall with full force.  He lay motionless on the grass while players rushed to his aid and policeman kept back the crowd.  Doc Woods ran up with a water bucket and medical bag.  Ruth had the wind wind knocked out of him and his left hip was badly bruised. Limping badly, he insisted on resuming his position despite Huggins' suggestion for a substitute.
The cheers for Ruth as he came to bat increased when he ran out the double in obvious pain.
Both Mogridge and McNulty missed the bag and McNulty was out when Mogridge touched him out in right field.
Speaker rounded third but when Goslin made a lucky stop of the ball, he tried to get back to third but was out.
McNulty threw to Burns who tagged Rice so hard on the leg he swung away from the bag; Hildebrand wouldn't allow the out.
Ruel turned his ankle sliding into 2B
Goslin tried to make a one-handed catch
Fewster booted Bluege's grounder but recovered it and retired Peck at third.
Good stop & fast throw by Judge who then hustled back to 1B
Rice dropped it but scored a double
Hit the top of RF wall
ej,harrb106,M,holmd102,Arguing balls and strikes $With a count of 2 & 1 to Speaker, Harris was ejected by Ump Holmes for arguing balls & strikes.

$When the game ended, excited fans poured on the field and surrounded Ump Holmes.  While one fan shook his finger at the umpire another struck him in the face, knocking him against a wall.  Ump Moriarty, players, and police came to the rescue.  A crowd of several thousands was then dispersed by a squad of blucoats.
Myatt was hit in the throat by a foul ball.  Time was called while he was given first aid.
Myatt leaned over into a field box
The Nationals argued it was foul
Sisler was caught in a rundown but got back to 2B.  McManus was nailed sliding into 2B.

$From this point to the end of the game there was a drizzling rain, but was never hard enough to stop play.

Great try by Mostil; his peg made a close play at 2B

Diving try by McNeely; Ump Evans first ruled it a catch so Collins had to retreat back to 1B, but when McNeely got to his feet without the ball, Evans reversed the decision and Collins was forced out. The White Sox played the rest of the game under protest and formally filed one with the league office after the game.
Archdeacon tried to score when the hard hit caromed off McNeely's shins.
Originally scheduled as 1st game of doubleheader. It was sprinkling as the teams took the field.
Gerber fouled off 6 pitches this AB
Walter was given a great round of applause as he came to bat
Rain began to fall as Goslin stepped to the plate
$Time was called as the Browns came to bat in the 8th.  After a half hour, Ump Nallin called the game on account of rain. 2nd game of scheduled doubleheader was postponed.
High off RF wall; good try by Rice
Spectacular 1-handed diving catch after misjudging it
Fine stop of bad-bounding hot one
A shower of straw hats followed the 2-run hit
Several more straw hats were thrown from the stands
Bad hop caromed off Peck's head
Close play at 3B; Senators put up a loud howl at Ump Holmes. Play was suspended for several minutes during the argument.

Close play; Sisler slid under Ruel who landed on top of him. When Ump Nallin called him out, Sisler pushed Ruel off him and went after Nallin.  Then McManus got into it and had a few words with Ruel; it looked like a near free-for-all but nobody was hurt.
The game was temporarily halted to clear several hundred straw hats and seat cushions off the field.
